certGlobHttpProxy.name: certGlobHttpProxy
certGlobHttpProxy.description: This object specifies the HTTP proxy server which must be used to access the HTTP certificate servers defined. It takes either an IP-address or a fully qualified domain name.

certGlobSocksServer.name: certGlobSocksServer
certGlobSocksServer.description: This object specifies the SOCKS server which must be used to access the HTTP and LDAP certificate servers defined. It takes either an IP-address or a fully qualified domain name.

certGlobMaxCacheEntries.name: certGlobMaxCacheEntries
certGlobMaxCacheEntries.description: This object specifies the maximum number of certificate-cache entries allowed.

certGlobMaxPathLength.name: certGlobMaxPathLength
certGlobMaxPathLength.description: This object specifies the maximum number of intermediate CA certificates between a trusted root CA and a peer certificate accepted.

certGlobMaxRestarts.name: certGlobMaxRestarts
certGlobMaxRestarts.description: This object specifies the maximum number of restarts in one certificate search.

certGlobMaxCertValidity.name: certGlobMaxCertValidity
certGlobMaxCertValidity.description: This object specifies the maximum validity period of a certificate in seconds. A certificate will not be considered valid for a longer period of time even if its validity field specifies a longer period.

certGlobMaxCrlValidity.name: certGlobMaxCrlValidity
certGlobMaxCrlValidity.description: This object specifies the maximum validity period of a certificate revocation list in seconds. A crl will not be considered valid for a longer period of time even if its validity field specifies a longer period.

certGlobNegCachePeriod.name: certGlobNegCachePeriod
certGlobNegCachePeriod.description: This object specifies the period in seconds a certificate or crl search with a negative result will be remembered. Within this time, no new search will be performed for the same item.

certServerTable.name: certServerTable
certServerTable.description: The certServerTable contains the list of certificate servers used for certificate and crl requests.

certServerEntry.name: certServerEntry
certServerEntry.description: A certificate server entry defines the name of a certificate server together with the protocols used to access it.

certServerName.name: certServerName
certServerName.description: This object specifies the name of a certificate server.

certServerUrl.name: certServerUrl
certServerUrl.description: This object specifies the url used for accessing the certificate server. Syntax: [<scheme>:][//[<user>[:<password>]@]<host>[:<port>]]/[<path>] example: ldap://myname:mypass@ldap.ca.com:389/ .

certServerPreference.name: certServerPreference
certServerPreference.description: This object specifies the preference of this server with respect to the others. Servers with lower priority are accessed prior to others.

certServerType.name: certServerType
certServerType.description: This object specifies the type of the entry and is used to delete it.

certTable.name: certTable
certTable.description: The certTable contains the list of certificates, including own certificates and those of the trusted certificate authorities.

certEntry.name: certEntry
certEntry.description: A certEntry contains either a peer's certificate, an own certficate or a certificate of a trusted certification authority, depending on the settings of the certFlags field.

certIndex.name: certIndex
certIndex.description: A unique index of this certificate entry.

certDescription.name: certDescription
certDescription.description: This object specifies the name of the X.509 Certificate.

certIsCA.name: certIsCA
certIsCA.description: This object specifies how the certificate is treated internally. Possible Values: true(1), -- A certificate of a trusted root CA false(2) -- An own or peer certificate.

certForceTrusted.name: certForceTrusted
certForceTrusted.description: This object specifies how the certificate is treated internally. Possible Values: true(1), -- Always trust this certificate without -- considering any CAs false(2) -- trust this certificate only, if there -- exists a valid trust path from a CA to it -- and it is not revoked.

certNoCrls.name: certNoCrls
certNoCrls.description: This object specifies how the certificate is treated internally. Possible Values: true(1), -- do not check for certificate revocation -- lists for this CA (no meaning for non-CA -- certificates) false(2) -- check for certificate revocation -- lists for this CA (no meaning for non-CA -- certificates).

certSerialNumber.name: certSerialNumber
certSerialNumber.description: This object specifies the serial number of the certificate.

certSubjectName.name: certSubjectName
certSubjectName.description: The subject name of the certificate.

certSubjectAltNames.name: certSubjectAltNames
certSubjectAltNames.description: The subject alternative name of the certificate. For IPSec, this field (not the subject name) is taken by default as the peer id, if not otherwise specified.

certIssuerName.name: certIssuerName
certIssuerName.description: The name of the certificate authority which issued this certificate.

certIssuerAltNames.name: certIssuerAltNames
certIssuerAltNames.description: The alternative names of the certificate authority which issued this certificate.

certValidity.name: certValidity
certValidity.description: The validity period of this certificate in human readable form.

certPubKeyInfo.name: certPubKeyInfo
certPubKeyInfo.description: This string shows the properties of the public key certified in this certificate. These are the algorithm for which the key is used and its length.

certKeyId.name: certKeyId
certKeyId.description: The key id as contained in the extensions of the certificate, if any.

certPrivateKey.name: certPrivateKey
certPrivateKey.description: The index of the private key from the ipsecPublicKeyTable corresponding to the public key in this certificate. Used only for own certificates.

certMD5Fingerprint.name: certMD5Fingerprint
certMD5Fingerprint.description: The fingerprint of the certificate computed as an MD5 hash of the DER encoded binary certificate data.

certSHA1Fingerprint.name: certSHA1Fingerprint
certSHA1Fingerprint.description: The fingerprint of the certificate computed as an SHA1 hash of the DER encoded binary certificate data.

certRevListTable.name: certRevListTable
certRevListTable.description: The certRevListTable contains the dynamic list of certificate revocation lists currently cached by the system.

certRevListEntry.name: certRevListEntry
certRevListEntry.description: This object describes a certificate revocation list (CRL) currently in the systems dynamic CRL cache.

certRevListIndex.name: certRevListIndex
certRevListIndex.description: A unique index of this CRL.

certRevListDescription.name: certRevListDescription
certRevListDescription.description: This object specifies the name of the certificate revocation list.

certRevListIssuerName.name: certRevListIssuerName
certRevListIssuerName.description: The name of the certificate authority which issued this CRL.

certRevListIssuerAltNames.name: certRevListIssuerAltNames
certRevListIssuerAltNames.description: The alternative names of the certificate authority which issued this CRL.

certRevListSerialNumber.name: certRevListSerialNumber
certRevListSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the CRL.

certRevListValidity.name: certRevListValidity
certRevListValidity.description: The issuing date of this CRL and the date the issuer is willing to issue the net update in human readable form.

certRevListNumCerts.name: certRevListNumCerts
certRevListNumCerts.description: The number of certificates contained in the CRL defined by this entry.
